\begin_layout Subsection
How to Blow the Whistle
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blowing the whistle is much similar to that of playing a wind instrument
 (since it is a wind instrument).
 Air pressure must be built in the lungs before a sound should be made.
 Use the tongue to stop the flow of air into the whistle by placing it on
 the opening of the whistle.
 Quickly release and repress the tongue on the mouthpiece of the whistle
 while maintaining air pressure to create a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

tweet.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 With practice this will sound more natural.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is possible to manipulate the pitch of the tone by lowering and raising
 the air pressure into the whistle.
 This is used in different patterns to indicate messages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Whistle Patterns
